    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "According to H. N. Caller, secretary\nof the International Coal & Coke COM\npany, which is engaged in development\nwork at Coleman on the Crows Mes\nPass railroad, the company has just\nawarded the contract for the erection\nof l04 coke ovens. One hundred tons\nis the daily output. Next spring 300\nadditional coke ovens will be built. At\nthat time the company will be employ\ning 900 men. Coke will be shipped to\nthe CRANKY smelter and also to Amer\nlean markets in general."
    }
  ]
